{"author":{"id":"b78c39e7b13f90a5827abfba043255fe7a4ede1499df23f110fffe5abfa44adc"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1769467310,"nonce":"wn+DDf8V25dEZD4ya3deOuT61dU=","metadata":{"github-id":"I_kwDOQ241x87l9DiY","github-url":"https://github.com/rolker/ros2_agent_workspace/issues/44","origin":"github"},"title":"Enforce Temporary File Policies and Git Hygiene","message":"## Description\nIt has been observed that agents are occasionally creating temporary files within package source directories and failing to clean them up. Subsequently, other agents are mistakenly committing these files to the repository.\n\n## Relevant Documentation\n- **.agent/rules/common/clean-root.md**: Specifies that temporary files should be placed in `./ai_workspace` or `/tmp`.\n- **AGENTS.md**: explicitly advises against modifying `workspaces/*/src/` unless instructed.\n\n## Proposed Solutions\n1. **Update .gitignore**: Add patterns to ignore common temporary files and directories at the workspace root.\n2. **Refine Agent Rules**: Update `clean-root.md` to explicitly forbid temp files in source directories (not just root).\n3. **Pre-commit Checks**: Implement a check in the commit workflow to warn about untracked files that look like temporary artifacts.\n4. **Agent Instruction**: Remind agents to use `git status` carefully and exclude unrelated files before committing.","files":null}]}